# Maintain and update Cursor rules

Applies when changing files under `.cursor/rules/ai-rules/`. For format and placement, see [write-cursor-rules-for-this-project.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/ai-rules/write-cursor-rules-for-this-project.mdc).

## Add a new rule when

- A pattern shows up in roughly **3+ places** and agents should default to it.
- A preventable bug class keeps appearing.
- Reviews repeat the same concrete request.

## Change a rule when

- Better examples exist in the repo than the rule shows.
- Edge cases or APIs changed and the text is stale.
- Another rule was split or renamed—fix references.

## Quality bar

- Actionable bullets, not slogans.
- Examples short and realistic; ❌/✅ only when it prevents misreads.
- One concern per file; split when the file is hard to scan (~50 lines is a good ceiling).

## Deprecation

- Mark outdated guidance clearly; remove rules that no longer apply.
- Update links pointing at renamed/removed rules.
- Add a one-line migration hint when behavior changed.

## Keep docs in sync

- Examples match current APIs and folder layout.
- External links still resolve; prefer stable URLs.
